            <thetext>Steps to reproduce:

1) Change e.g. font background and text color
2) write text
3) insert image
4) write more text

The resulting HTML will be:

--snip--
&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 102, 0); background-color: rgb(0, 255, 0);&quot;&gt;write text&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;IMAGEURL&quot; title=&quot; &quot; alt=&quot; &quot; id=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;19&quot; width=&quot;19&quot;&gt;write more text
--snip--

Since the trailing text node is not encapsulated with a span tag it falls back to the default settings (ruled by the body element).</thetext>
